President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated his deputy, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo, as he celebrates his 63rd birthday In a telephone chat yesterday, the president commended Osinbajo’s loyalty and dedication to the administration. He noted that the intellectual capacity of the vice president had impacted positively on the overall accomplishments of the Federal Government. Also, the celebrant’s spokesman, Laolu Akande, eugolised his principal for being a role a model. He acknowledged yesterday that the number two citizen possesses four unique attributes, namely “the grace of God; the fear of God; relentless hardworking ethos and a tremendous understanding of strategy and timing.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .